body.text: Alex, Duterte has absolute dictatorial power over his "war on drugs".  The nation's Head Chief of police is his puppet and so are the thousands of leutenants spearheading each town and cities.   There is no due process or any investigation, nor there is checks and balances by the congress over human rights abuse.  The sad part is that 90% of those killed are not "pushers" but mostly speculated "users" who succomed to their addiction.  Instead of wishing and hoping for the UN to hand down an indictment...  A pro active solution would be for a non-profit to start building rehab clinics that can take in these "users" and also train these young able bodied men skillsets that they can use to replace their "idle" time and help provide for their families.

body.text: Alex, If all Middle class Americans took a poll right now, 99% would say that they're biggest threat is Housing, Healthcare & the future of Social Security.  The Geopolitical threat of Russia, N. Korea and any Middle eastern countries that has potential to harbor terrorist... is the last thing that every hard working American Family worry about.  Yet, most of America's resources is allocated on buying F-35 Fighter Jets at $90 mil. a piece that cost 20k in jet fuel to fly around (just for drills) fattening up Lockheed Martin's pockets... while there are more than 65,000 homeless Americans sleeping in the streets of NYC alone.  Cheers.

body.text: Alex, Its going to take plenty of effort to cut down on deforestation in the Amazon (no pun intended).  First, the Brazilian gov. needs to make some effort in facilitating safety for the tribal communities that consider the Amazon part of their Habitat.  Second, with Brazil being a commodity based economy which relies highly on their raw materials & Minerals (ea. lumber, rubber, mining)...  there has to be an aggressive effort on their Fed gov. to  REPLACE used resources (whether done by the gov. or a private entity)... Cut a tree down.. plant a tree somewhere.   Third, with the Amazon being the "lungs" of planet earth (taking in the Co2/carbon and pushing out O2)  There has to be an aggresive push by the Global Leaders to put pressure on the Brazilian law makers.  Right now Brazil is having a slow economic growth since there markets haven't still fully recovered from the recession.  The Brazilian gov. is speculating highly on Infrastructure/Building in the hopes of pumping up jobs and revenue,  for the price of deforestation and eventually losing the AMAZON.

body.text: Alex, I think proper Policing goes back to 'Competency'...  A rookie 25 yr. old cop has such a high level of INcompetency to be allowed to have a deadly weapon more less having full autonomy to use it.   As a minority myself, It is somewhat scary to interact with an anxious over caffeinated and over-aggressive rookie cop.  It's sad as a law-abiding taxpayer, to fear the same people that is suppose to make you feel safe.  I believe that a solution is for each City municipality or Local county to hold mandatory monthly trainings that educate & train them on proper "mindful" interactions (and minimizing use of deadly force)...  Also they need to try to reach out to the Community and build trust and Rapport, especially with the younger minority population.   Also, every single cop in the Country needs to have a body-cam which can be as simple as a gopro cam strap in the vest (if police departments can afford brand new Dodge Chargers for everyone, why can't they afford a $100 dollar camera)...  this would help bring in transparency and accountability which helps build trust from the public,      Cheers.
